  "prompt": "What should be my 12th board percentage to get admission in St. Xavier's College Autonomous, Mumbai for B.Com?",
  "response": "Admission to St. Xavier's College (Autonomous), Mumbai, for the Bachelor of Commerce (B.Com) program typically requires a competitive percentage in your 12th board examinations, usually from a recognized board. While specific percentage cut-offs can vary each year based on the applicant pool, a general guideline is that students often need to have at least 80% or above in their 12th-grade exams for a strong chance of admission.\n\nHowever, it's essential to check the college's official website or contact the admissions office for the most accurate and updated information regarding cut-offs and admission criteria for the current academic year.",
